## ğŸ”‘ Environment Variables
Create a `.env` file in the root directory and add the following:

PORT ="7000"
CLIENT_URL="http://localhost:5173"
MONGODB_URL="mongodb+srv://adil:Adil%40953947@cluster0.lfvmsb8.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=Cluster0"
REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET="Adil@123"
ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET="Adil@123"

LOG_INTERVAL="7d"
NODE_ENV="production"



# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/aadil-nv/Book-Management.git

# Move into the project folder
cd Book-Management

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run in development mode
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Start production server
npm start



